## Hints for Future Agents
- `git notes` are a separate ref (`refs/notes/commits`). They don't push or
  fetch with normal `git push` / `git pull`. Use:
    git push origin refs/notes/commits
    git fetch origin refs/notes/*:refs/notes/*
- To always show notes in `git log`, set:
    git config --global notes.displayRef refs/notes/commits
  (or pass `--show-notes` on demand).
- `git log --show-notes` shows every commit's note inline. Without that flag
  you'll think notes are missing.
- Notes attach to the *commit SHA*, so a rebase / squash-merge orphans them.
  Add notes AFTER the squash-merge lands on main, not before, otherwise the
  note follows the original branch commit which gets garbage-collected.

## Codebase Discoveries
- AGENTS.md uses Claude Code's @-import syntax (e.g. `@rules/simple.md`) and
  CLAUDE.md just contains `@AGENTS.md`. So we have a 2-hop import chain:
  CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md → rules/*.md. Load is automatic per session.
- The repo has 30+ stale agent worktrees under `.claude/worktrees/`. `git
  worktree list` shows them all locked. They accumulated from each agent
  dispatch; nothing prunes them. Worth a sweep at some point but not urgent.

